	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually, I don't know what level you are, but if you don't know where to find it, you probably can't use it yet, and won't be able to for a while.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you click on your Alternate Advancement button in your inventory (if you have Luclin), and page over to the Class-specific abilities (the level 59+ ones), you'll find Mana Burn.  Yes, that's right, you have to be level 59 (or it might even be 60, not sure), to use Mana Burn, and you have to buy several other A.A. abilities before you can even touch this one.  Oooooh, but is it ever worth it ;)  You do an amount of damage based on your mana, which at level 60 with 250 INT, *whew*... I've heard of Critical Nukes for 18,000+ damage on one use (of course it's also a couple hours on the re-cast time).  A group of Mana Burn Wizards can knock down uber mobs in literally seconds.  So keep working and you'll one day get to use this ability.<br>&nbsp;<br>Daebin Ghelaric - 57 Human Outrider &lt;Elder Tribunal&gt;<br>Maurill Dillemma - 35 Wood Elf Druid &lt;Elder Tribunal&gt;<br>Cassilia Hyades - 28 High Elf Cleric<br>Josiif Joinauty - 24 Erudite Enchanter</td></tr>
