	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.34]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>np man..here ya go.. i will try to say this with clarity but with out showing someone it is a little hard =P<br>ok..first off goto EW on the north shore of the zone almost to GD youll find an indented fort of rygorr and giants.. *these are not what you kite*<br>around that fort youll find uthork hunters and uthork warriors.. the warriors are the stronger of the two..and i suggest that you stick to hunters until you feel more comfortable with kiting.. <br>on one side of this area by the water youll see a spawning area for uthorks walrus's and rhinos.. that is your farming area..as well as the area around the fort.. but becareful not to get to close to the fort so you dont draw added agro..<br>on the opposite side by the shoreline theres a BIG open field nothing spawns here making it the perfect area for kiting because there will be no adds.. and you can med by the shoreline with out worry of drawing agro.. <br>what i did to make it easier for me as well .. if u walk down the shoreline toward GD zone youll find a hut of coldains.. bind somewhere here where nothing is spawning.. that way if u die *(which not to burst ur bubble but it may happen alot at first lol)* you can easily get back to corpse and also gate to bind to get away from added mobs or the outta mana blues<br>you will need to have circle of force as your aoe.. bonds of force as your bonding spell .. a DD spell of your choice for finishing.. because sometimes you get a little low on mana for that last shot on the last uthork.. also for your protection put up &quot;yonder&quot; and &quot;gate&quot; i can not stress these two spells enough while kiting..they are in fact the most important spells for living a long prosperous life as a wiz =P<br>the other spells are your choice.. of course harvest and whatever else u feel you need<br>if you do not have jboots you will need to buy sow potions or have someone sow you up.. ill give ya a new trick to kiting and this one.. <br>instead of spending bucks on sow potions.. get your nexus portal ..and gate to nexus regularly and bum a sow off someone =)..theres alot of classes that can sow and most people are more then happy to help.. if your really lucky someone will be up there with KEI which is an int buff and mana regen buff from a lvl 60 chanter.. VERY nice to have<br>ok.. you say ur all sowed up? u have kei? your spells loaded? ur bound? woot your ready to kite!<br><br>now to start this off til u get comfortable.. grab 2 hunters.. dont get greedy.. til you see how much mana u burn and how good u are.. <br>if you have the staff of flux.. *very nice to have for kiting* pull with it.. if not.. use a low lvl DD spell one that using like 20m to cast to pull the agro <br>build ur 2 uthorks and bring them to the nice open field.. do not bond them until they are all together.. if u do youll end up with one chasing u fast another chasing you slow.. pain in the butt to get em back together.. although u will need to learn this tatic as well *threading the needle is what i call it*<br>once they are nice and together get a good distance from them.. until your just outta casting range.. this range will have to be felt by u.. youll get used to it.. takes a little time.. unless you have staff of flux in which case jus cast it until its outta range then you know your safe to stop and cast bonds of force<br>cast your bonds and hopefully they both hit.. they will both slow down .. now run again a little farther away so you have enough distance to cast circle of force.. repeat this method and wa la your kiting.. eventually youll feel better about this and next thing you know youll be building 3 and 4 kites.. my personal best is 7 but.. i also wa a wee bit lucky =)and i didnt do it til lvl 42 or so..<br>the xp here is RAGIN good almost 2 blues for every quad at lvl 34.. its very nice to see .. ull feel lvl 18 again =P<br>one last thing.. if u decide to kite here in ew the loot can be very nice as well.. <br>occasionally youll run across uthork tusks.. keep them.. four of them turned into the chief othmir in CS (cobalt scar) is good for a gem reward of worth from anywhere from 100pp to 3k pp .. sometimes a gag gift like crystalized sulfur.. pisses ya off but dont nuke him hehe. he dont like it =x<br>good luck to you!!! <br>i hope this helps a little bit.. if u die a few times dont get frustrated the xp is so good dying really doesnt matter much lol.. in the time you run to the rygorr fort for a 90% rez .. you coulda kited the xp back heh.. so jus keep kiting!!<br>take care~~<br>taygarr <br>wiz of the 55th season<br>the seventh hammer<br><br>&quot;ohhh i manaburned my wittle finga!&quot;<br><br>&nbsp;<br>WIZROG!!!!!!!!</td></tr>
